    "b-theme-palette-roles-5": {
      "id": "b-theme-palette-roles-5",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The model is three roles per hue. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "Ink",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is the line-safe stroke color: picker swatches use it, and shapes, connectors, and section title-chip borders all stroke with it. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "Fill",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is the object/chip body color, with stickies keeping their own hue-specific fill from the same family. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "Wash",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is the lightest expression — the section background tint, kept lighter than any object so contained objects stay legible. Line-safety is why the inks deviate from naive saturation: yellow, orange, and gray reuse FigJam's sampled connector strokes (#E8A302, #EB7500, #757575) so a 2px line still reads against the #F5F5F5 board."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
